        "text": "This article is over 15 years old and may contain outdated information\n\nRecommended Videos\n\nDespite being absent at E3 Tecmo plans on releasing the Rygar on the Wii in North America this December. Don’t get too excited, Rygar: The Battle of Argus is not a new entry in the series, it’s a remake of Rygar: The Legendary Adventure which Tecmo released for the PS2 in 2002. The game has been updated with additional enemies, techniques, and of course motion control for Diskarmor throwing . A new for the Wii gladiator mode is designed specifically for “the versatile swinging movement of the Wii remote.” I hope this isn’t a multiplayer shakefest.\n\nFunny, Nintendo of Europe just announced Disaster: Day of Crisis too. Today must be the day where nearly forgotten Wii games rear their heads.\n\nImages courtesy of Tecmo."
